entry.def: Legal proceedings are legal action taken against someone.

example.ex: ...criminal proceedings against the former prime minister...
The Council had brought proceedings to stop the store from trading on Sundays.
example.tran: 该委员会已经提起诉讼，禁止这家商店在周日营业。

entry.tran: （有组织的一系列）活动，事件，行动
entry.def: The proceedings are an organized series of events that take place in a particular place.

example.ex: The proceedings of the enquiry will take place in private...
He viewed the proceedings with doubt and alarm.
example.tran: 他带着怀疑和警觉的眼光看待这些事件。

entry.def: You can refer to a written record of the discussions at a meeting or conference as the proceedings.

example.ex: The Department of Transport is to publish the conference proceedings.
example.tran: 交通部将公布这次会议的记录。

means.word_mean: 1. (law) the institution of a sequence of steps by which legal judgments are invoked
2. a written account of what transpired at a meeting
